race.comment: REAL ALLIANCE (5) disappointed as a $2.5 favourite at Great Western and prepared to forgive that. Was only beaten 3.5 lengths at Flemington prior off strong provincial efforts. Should enjoy the significant drop in grade. Best form puts her right in this. Has the handy 2kg claim for a 2x winning rider and this is a suitable assignment. HIS FINEST HOUR (6) is a big threat building on his two narrow defeats at Flemington. Maps well enough and should go close. FEARGAL (8) can control; the race from the handy barrier and has missed narrowly at Warrnambool his last two. He's sure to take pegging back. FRIDAY AT FIVE (9) has an awkward barrier but has been threatening a win and sits down in the weights. FOX APPEAL (3) would have claims on his Flemington effort two back.
